#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:4
msgid "cmake-presets(7)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:7
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:11
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:15
msgid ""
"One problem that CMake users often face is sharing settings with other "
"people for common ways to configure a project. This may be done to support "
"CI builds, or for users who frequently use the same build. CMake supports "
"two main files, ``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json``, that "
"allow users to specify common configure options and share them with others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:23
msgid ""
"CMake also supports files included with the :preset:`include` field.  See "
"`Includes`_ for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:26
msgid ""
"``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` live in the project's "
"root directory. They both have exactly the same format, and both are "
"optional (though at least one must be present if :cmake-option:`--preset` is "
"specified).  ``CMakePresets.json`` is meant to specify project-wide build "
"details, while ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` is meant for developers to specify "
"their own local build details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:33
msgid ""
"``CMakePresets.json`` may be checked into a version control system, and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` should NOT be checked in. For example, if a "
"project is using Git, ``CMakePresets.json`` may be tracked, and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` should be added to the ``.gitignore``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:40
msgid ""
"CMake also supports specifying a file from which to read presets via the :"
"cmake-option:`--presets-file` option.  If this option is specified, neither "
"of ``CMakePresets.json`` nor ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` are required to be "
"present, and any presets defined in those files will be ignored/unavailable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:46
msgid "Format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:48
msgid "The files are a JSON document with an object as the root:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:50
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"version\": 10,\n"
"  \"cmakeMinimumRequired\": {\n"
"    \"major\": 3,\n"
"    \"minor\": 23,\n"
"    \"patch\": 0\n"
"  },\n"
"  \"$comment\": \"An example CMakePresets.json file\",\n"
"  \"include\": [\n"
"    \"otherThings.json\",\n"
"    \"moreThings.json\"\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"configurePresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"$comment\": [\n"
"        \"This is a comment row.\",\n"
"        \"This is another comment,\",\n"
"        \"just because we can do it\"\n"
"      ],\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"displayName\": \"Default Config\",\n"
"      \"description\": \"Default build using Ninja generator\",\n"
"      \"generator\": \"Ninja\",\n"
"      \"binaryDir\": \"${sourceDir}/build/default\",\n"
"      \"cacheVariables\": {\n"
"        \"FIRST_CACHE_VARIABLE\": {\n"
"          \"type\": \"BOOL\",\n"
"          \"value\": \"OFF\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"SECOND_CACHE_VARIABLE\": \"ON\"\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"environment\": {\n"
"        \"MY_ENVIRONMENT_VARIABLE\": \"Test\",\n"
"        \"PATH\": \"$env{HOME}/ninja/bin:$penv{PATH}\"\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"vendor\": {\n"
"        \"example.com/ExampleIDE/1.0\": {\n"
"          \"autoFormat\": true\n"
"        }\n"
"      }\n"
"    },\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"ninja-multi\",\n"
"      \"inherits\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"displayName\": \"Ninja Multi-Config\",\n"
"      \"description\": \"Default build using Ninja Multi-Config "
"generator\",\n"
"      \"generator\": \"Ninja Multi-Config\"\n"
"    },\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"windows-only\",\n"
"      \"inherits\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"displayName\": \"Windows-only configuration\",\n"
"      \"description\": \"This build is only available on Windows\",\n"
"      \"condition\": {\n"
"        \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"        \"lhs\": \"${hostSystemName}\",\n"
"        \"rhs\": \"Windows\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"buildPresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"configurePreset\": \"default\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"testPresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"configurePreset\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"output\": {\"outputOnFailure\": true},\n"
"      \"execution\": {\"noTestsAction\": \"error\", \"stopOnFailure\": "
"true}\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"packagePresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"configurePreset\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"generators\": [\n"
"        \"TGZ\"\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"workflowPresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"steps\": [\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"type\": \"configure\",\n"
"          \"name\": \"default\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"type\": \"build\",\n"
"          \"name\": \"default\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"type\": \"test\",\n"
"          \"name\": \"default\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"type\": \"package\",\n"
"          \"name\": \"default\"\n"
"        }\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"vendor\": {\n"
"    \"example.com/ExampleIDE/1.0\": {\n"
"      \"autoFormat\": false\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:55
msgid ""
"Presets files may include comments using the key ``$comment`` at any level "
"within the JSON object to provide documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:58
msgid "The root object recognizes the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:6
msgid "``$schema``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:9
msgid ""
"An optional string that provides a URI to the JSON schema that describes the "
"structure of this JSON document. This field is used for validation and "
"autocompletion in editors that support JSON schema. It doesn't affect the "
"behavior of the document itself. If this field is not specified, the JSON "
"document will still be valid, but tools that use JSON schema for validation "
"and autocompletion may not function correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:13
msgid "``version``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:14
msgid ""
"A required integer representing the version of the JSON schema. See "
"`Versions`_ for discussion of the supported versions and the corresponding "
"version of CMake in which they were added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:20
msgid "``cmakeMinimumRequired``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:21
msgid ""
"An optional object representing the minimum version of CMake needed to build "
"this project. This object consists of the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/cmakeMinimumRequired-properties.rst:6
msgid "``major``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/cmakeMinimumRequired-properties.rst:7
msgid "An optional integer representing the major version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/cmakeMinimumRequired-properties.rst:11
msgid "``minor``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/cmakeMinimumRequired-properties.rst:12
msgid "An optional integer representing the minor version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/cmakeMinimumRequired-properties.rst:16
msgid "``patch``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/cmakeMinimumRequired-properties.rst:17
msgid "An optional integer representing the patch version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/filter-properties.rst:6
#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:29
msgid "``include``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:32
msgid ""
"An optional array of strings representing files to include. If the filenames "
"are not absolute, they are considered relative to the current file. See "
"`Includes`_ for discussion of the constraints on included files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:53
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:52
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:50
#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:39
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:52
#: ../../../manual/presets/workflowPresets-properties.rst:17
msgid "``vendor``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:40
msgid ""
"An optional map containing vendor-specific information. CMake does not "
"interpret the contents of this field except to verify that it is a map if it "
"does exist. However, the keys should be a vendor-specific domain name "
"followed by a ``/``-separated path. For example, the Example IDE 1.0 could "
"use ``example.com/ExampleIDE/1.0``. The value of each field can be anything "
"desired by the vendor, though will typically be a map."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:49
msgid "``configurePresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:50
msgid "An optional array of `Configure Preset`_ objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:54
msgid "``buildPresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:57
msgid "An optional array of `Build Preset`_ objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:61
msgid "``testPresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:64
msgid "An optional array of `Test Preset`_ objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:68
msgid "``packagePresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:71
msgid "An optional array of `Package Preset`_ objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:75
msgid "``workflowPresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/root-properties.rst:78
msgid "An optional array of `Workflow Preset`_ objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:63
msgid "Includes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:67
msgid ""
"CMake presets files can include other files with the :preset:`include` "
"field. Files included in this manner can also include other files.  If "
"``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` are both present, "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` implicitly includes ``CMakePresets.json``, even "
"with no :preset:`include` field, in all versions of the format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:73
msgid ""
"If a presets file contains presets that inherit from presets in another "
"file, the file must include the other file either directly or indirectly. "
"Include cycles are not allowed among files. If ``a.json`` includes ``b."
"json``, ``b.json`` cannot include ``a.json``. However, a file may be "
"included multiple times from the same file or from different files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:79
msgid ""
"Files directly or indirectly included from ``CMakePresets.json`` should be "
"guaranteed to be provided by the project. ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` may "
"include files from anywhere."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:85
msgid ""
"The :preset:`include` field supports `macro expansion`_, but only ``$penv{}"
"`` macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:90
msgid ""
"The :preset:`include` field supports `macro expansion`_, except for ``$env{}"
"`` and preset-specific macros (i.e., those derived from the fields inside a "
"preset's definition like ``presetName``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:97
msgid "Configure Preset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:99
msgid ""
"Each entry of the ``configurePresets`` array is a JSON object that may "
"contain the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:6
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:6
#: ../../../manual/presets/exclude-properties.rst:6
#: ../../../manual/presets/include-properties.rst:6
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:6
#: ../../../manual/presets/steps-properties.rst:13
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:6
#: ../../../manual/presets/workflowPresets-properties.rst:6
msgid "``name``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:7
msgid ""
"A required string representing the machine-friendly name of the preset. This "
"identifier is used in the :option:`cmake --preset` option. There must not be "
"two configure presets in the union of ``CMakePresets.json`` and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` in the same directory with the same name. However, "
"a configure preset may have the same name as a build, test, package, or "
"workflow preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:17
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:16
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:16
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:16
msgid "``hidden``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:17
msgid ""
"An optional boolean specifying whether or not a preset should be hidden. If "
"a preset is hidden, it cannot be used in the :cmake-option:`--preset` "
"argument, will not show up in the :manual:`CMake GUI <cmake-gui(1)>`, and "
"does not have to have a valid ``generator`` or ``binaryDir``, even from "
"inheritance. ``hidden`` presets are intended to be used as a base for other "
"presets to inherit via the ``inherits`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:28
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:27
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:27
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:27
msgid "``inherits``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:29
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:28
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:28
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:28
msgid ""
"An optional array of strings representing the names of presets from which to "
"inherit. This field can also be a string, which is equivalent to an array "
"containing one string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:33
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:32
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:32
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:32
msgid ""
"The preset will inherit all of the fields from the ``inherits`` presets by "
"default (except ``name``, ``hidden``, ``inherits``, ``description``, and "
"``displayName``), but can override them as desired. If multiple ``inherits`` "
"presets provide conflicting values for the same field, the earlier preset in "
"the ``inherits`` array will be preferred."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:39
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:38
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:38
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:38
msgid ""
"A preset can only inherit from another preset that is defined in the same "
"file or in one of the files it includes (directly or indirectly). Presets in "
"``CMakePresets.json`` may not inherit from presets in ``CMakeUserPresets."
"json``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:224
#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:46
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:45
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:45
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:45
msgid "``condition``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/buildPresets-properties.rst:49
#: ../../../manual/presets/configurePresets-properties.rst:48
#: ../../../manual/presets/packagePresets-properties.rst:46
#: ../../../manual/presets/testPresets-properties.rst:48
msgid "An optional `Condition`_ object."
