msgid ""
"Set the respective value. This will result in an error for generators that "
"do not support the respective field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/architecture-properties.rst:19
#: ../../../manual/presets/toolset-properties.rst:19
msgid "``\"external\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/presets/architecture-properties.rst:20
#: ../../../manual/presets/toolset-properties.rst:20
msgid ""
"Do not set the value, even if the generator supports it. This is useful if, "
"for example, a preset uses the Ninja generator, and an IDE knows how to set "
"up the Visual C++ environment from the architecture and toolset fields. In "
"that case, CMake will ignore the field, but the IDE can use them to set up "
"the environment before invoking CMake."
msgstr ""

