#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:153
msgid "Condition"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:157
msgid ""
"The ``condition`` field of a preset is used to determine whether or not the "
"preset is enabled. For example, this can be used to disable a preset on "
"platforms other than Windows. ``condition`` may be either a boolean, "
"``null``, or an object. If it is a boolean, the boolean indicates whether "
"the preset is enabled or disabled. If it is ``null``, the preset is enabled, "
"but the ``null`` condition is not inherited by any presets that may inherit "
"from the preset. Sub-conditions (for example in a ``not``, ``anyOf``, or "
"``allOf`` condition) may not be ``null``. If it is an object, it has the "
"following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:167
msgid "A required string with one of the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:169
msgid "``\"const\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:170
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition is constant. This is equivalent to using a "
"boolean in place of the object. The condition object will have the following "
"additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:175
msgid ""
"A required boolean which provides a constant value for the condition's "
"evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:178
msgid "``\"equals\"``, ``\"notEquals\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:179
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition compares two strings to see if they are equal "
"(or not equal). The condition object will have the following additional "
"fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:183
msgid "``lhs``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:184
msgid "First string to compare. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:186
msgid "``rhs``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:187
msgid "Second string to compare. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:189
msgid "``\"inList\"``, ``\"notInList\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:190
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition searches for a string in a list of strings. The "
"condition object will have the following additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:193
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:204
msgid "``string``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:194
msgid "A required string to search for. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:196
msgid "``list``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:197
msgid ""
"A required array of strings to search. This field supports macro expansion, "
"and uses short-circuit evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:200
msgid "``\"matches\"``, ``\"notMatches\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:201
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition searches for a regular expression in a string. "
"The condition object will have the following additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:205
msgid "A required string to search. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:207
msgid "``regex``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:208
msgid ""
"A required regular expression to search for. This field supports macro "
"expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:211
msgid "``\"anyOf\"``, ``\"allOf\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:213
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition is an aggregation of zero or more nested "
"conditions. The condition object will have the following additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:216
msgid "``conditions``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:217
msgid ""
"A required array of condition objects. These conditions use short-circuit "
"evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:220
msgid "``\"not\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:221
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition is an inversion of another condition. The "
"condition object will have the following additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:225
msgid "A required condition object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:228
msgid "Macro Expansion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:230
msgid ""
"As mentioned above, some fields support macro expansion. Macros are "
"recognized in the form ``$<macro-namespace>{<macro-name>}``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:233
msgid ""
"In general, macros are evaluated in the context of the preset being used, "
"even if the macro is in a field that was inherited from another preset. For "
"example, if the ``Base`` preset sets variable ``PRESET_NAME`` to "
"``${presetName}``, and the ``Derived`` preset inherits from ``Base``, "
"``PRESET_NAME`` will be set to ``Derived``. The ``${fileDir}`` macro as of "
"preset version ``12`` is an exception to this rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:240
msgid ""
"It is an error to not put a closing brace at the end of a macro name. For "
"example, ``${sourceDir`` is invalid. A dollar sign (``$``) followed by "
"anything other than a left curly brace (``{``) with a possible namespace is "
"interpreted as a literal dollar sign."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:245
msgid "Recognized macros include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:247
msgid "``${sourceDir}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:248
msgid ""
"Path to the project source directory (i.e. the same as :variable:"
"`CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:251
msgid "``${sourceParentDir}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:252
msgid "Path to the project source directory's parent directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:254
msgid "``${sourceDirName}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:255
msgid ""
"The last filename component of ``${sourceDir}``. For example, if "
"``${sourceDir}`` is ``/path/to/source``, this would be ``source``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:258
msgid "``${presetName}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:259
msgid "Name specified in the preset's ``name`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:261
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:268
msgid "This is a preset-specific macro."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:263
msgid "``${generator}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:264
msgid ""
"Generator specified in the preset's ``generator`` field. For build and test "
"presets, this will evaluate to the generator specified by "
"``configurePreset``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:272
msgid "``${hostSystemName}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:275
msgid ""
"The name of the host operating system. Contains the same value as :variable:"
"`CMAKE_HOST_SYSTEM_NAME`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:280
msgid "``${fileDir}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:283
msgid ""
"Path to the directory containing the presets file which defines the preset "
"being used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:288
msgid ""
"This macro *always* expands to the directory of the current presets file "
"containing the macro, regardless of the preset being used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:291
msgid "For example, consider the following scenario."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:293
msgid ""
"``/path/to/CMakePresets.json`` includes ``/path/to/subdir/CMakePresets."
"json``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:295
msgid ""
"``/path/to/subdir/CMakePresets.json`` defines preset ``Base``, which sets "
"variable ``MY_DIR`` to ``${fileDir}``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:297
msgid ""
"``/path/to/CMakePresets.json`` defines preset ``Derived``, and ``Derived`` "
"inherits from ``Base``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:300
msgid ""
"Under preset versions ``4``-``11``, ``MY_DIR`` will be set to ``/path/to/`` "
"when using the ``Derived`` preset, and ``/path/to/subdir/`` when using the "
"``Base`` preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:304
msgid ""
"When ``/path/to/subdir/CMakePresets.json`` specifies version ``12`` or "
"above, ``MY_DIR`` will always be set to ``/path/to/subdir/``, regardless of "
"the preset being used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:310
msgid ""
"Since the ``${fileDir}`` macro in version 12 is expanded in the context of "
"the current presets file, it is the version of the current file, rather than "
"the version of the root file containing the preset being used, which "
"dictates this behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:315
msgid "``${dollar}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:316
msgid "A literal dollar sign (``$``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:320
msgid "``${pathListSep}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:323
msgid "Native character for separating lists of paths, such as ``:`` or ``;``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:325
msgid ""
"For example, by setting ``PATH`` to ``/path/to/ninja/"
"bin${pathListSep}$env{PATH}``, ``${pathListSep}`` will expand to the "
"underlying operating system's character used for concatenation in ``PATH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:330
msgid "``$env{<variable-name>}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:331
msgid ""
"Environment variable with name ``<variable-name>``. The variable name may "
"not be an empty string. If the variable is defined in the ``environment`` "
"field, that value is used instead of the value from the parent environment. "
"If the environment variable is not defined, this evaluates as an empty "
"string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:337
msgid ""
"Note that while Windows environment variable names are case-insensitive, "
"variable names within a preset are still case-sensitive. This may lead to "
"unexpected results when using inconsistent casing. For best results, keep "
"the casing of environment variable names consistent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:342
msgid "``$penv{<variable-name>}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:343
msgid ""
"Similar to ``$env{<variable-name>}``, except that the value only comes from "
"the parent environment, and never from the ``environment`` field. This "
"allows one to prepend or append values to existing environment variables. "
"For example, setting ``PATH`` to ``/path/to/ninja/bin:$penv{PATH}`` will "
"prepend ``/path/to/ninja/bin`` to the ``PATH`` environment variable. This is "
"needed because ``$env{<variable-name>}`` does not allow circular references."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:351
msgid "``$vendor{<macro-name>}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:352
msgid ""
"An extension point for vendors to insert their own macros. CMake will not be "
"able to use presets which have a ``$vendor{<macro-name>}`` macro, and "
"effectively ignores such presets. However, it will still be able to use "
"other presets from the same file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:357
msgid ""
"CMake does not make any attempt to interpret ``$vendor{<macro-name>}`` "
"macros. However, to avoid name collisions, IDE vendors should prefix "
"``<macro-name>`` with a very short (preferably <= 4 characters) vendor "
"identifier prefix, followed by a ``.``, followed by the macro name. For "
"example, the Example IDE could have ``$vendor{xide.ideInstallDir}``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:364
msgid "Versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:366
msgid ""
"The JSON schema of CMake presets files follows a version scheme where new "
"versions are added and allowed in newer versions of CMake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:369
msgid ""
"A list of the supported versions along with the version of CMake in which "
"they were added and a summary of the new features and changes is given below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:372
msgid "``1``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:375
msgid ""
"The initial version supports `Configure Presets <Configure Preset_>`_ and "
"`Macro Expansion`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:378
msgid "``2``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:381
msgid "`Build Presets <Build Preset_>`_ were added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:382
msgid "`Test Presets <Test Preset_>`_ were added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:384
msgid "``3``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:387
msgid ""
"The `Condition`_ object was added for `Configure <Configure Preset_>`_, "
"`Build <Build Preset_>`_, and `Test Presets <Test Preset_>`_."
msgstr ""

